Dear SSIN as an old ahjumah re-married for 28 years. In order to get along, your boyfriend needs to do everything in his power to make you happy and you have to do everything in your power to make him happy. If not, it's not going to last. Both people in a relationship need to worry about the other person's happiness, not their own. That way you can have a very long term partnership that will last well into your golden years. My first husband and I didn't do that with each other and it was no surprise that it didn't work out. It hurt like hell, but we didn't put in the effort equally.
